headline: Boeing and Sun PhuQuoc Airways Announce Order for Up to 40 787 Dreamliner Jets
summary: Boeing [NYSE: BA] and Sun PhuQuoc Airways today announced the new Vietnam-based carrier has ordered up to 40 787 Dreamliner jets to serve as the backbone of its widebody fleet. The airline will leverage the ultra-efficient, long-range 787 Dreamliner to connect international travelers to its Vietnam hub at Phu Quoc International Airport.

content.title: Boeing and Sun PhuQuoc Airways Announce Order for Up to 40 787 Dreamliner Jets

The airline will leverage the ultra-efficient, long-range 787 Dreamliner to connect international travelers to its Vietnam hub at Phu Quoc International Airport.

thumbnail.caption: Leaders of Sun Group and Sun PhuQuoc Airways joined Boeing at a ceremony in Washington, D.C. today to announce an order for up to 40 787 Dreamliner jets, which will serve as the backbone of the airline's widebody fleet. Flanked by cabin crew members are (left to right): Brad McMullen, Boeing senior vice president of Commercial Sales and Marketing; Stephanie Pope, president and CEO of Boeing Commercial Airplanes; Dang Minh Truong, chairman of Sun Group; and Tran Minh Son, deputy chairman of Sun Group.

headline: Vietnam Airlines Finalizes Order for 50 Boeing 737 MAX Airplanes
summary: Boeing [NYSE: BA] and Vietnam Airlines announced today the Vietnamese flag carrier finalized its first Boeing single-aisle order for 50 737 MAX airplanes. The addition of the 737-8 will enable Vietnam Airlines' domestic and regional route growth plans as air travel demand continues to rise across Southeast Asia.

thumbnail.caption: Vietnam and U.S. government officials joined Stephanie Pope, president and CEO of Boeing Commercial Airplanes, and Dang Ngoc Hoa, chairman of the Board of Directors of Vietnam Airlines, at a ceremony in Washington, D.C. today to announce an order for 50 737 MAX airplanes.

headline: Boeing Bags Orders for Almost 100 Jets From Vietnamese Carriers
summary: Boeing  signed deals to sell almost 100 jets to Vietnamese carriers valued at over $30 billion, signaling warming ties between the U.S. and Vietnam as trade talks continue.  The deals were signed during a ​visit to the U.S. by the head of Vietnam’s Communist Party, To Lam, for the inaugural meeting of President Trump’s Board of Peace.  The aircraft maker struck a $22.5 billion deal to sell up to 40 787-9 Dreamliners to Vietnam-based carrier Sun PhuQuoc Airways.

headline: Boeing Rival Airbus’ Stock Drops After Earnings Beat. This Is The Big Problem.
summary: Shares of  Boeing  peer  Airbus  were down 7% in overseas trading on Thursday after the company reported better-than-expected fourth-quarter earnings.  For 2026, however, Airbus expects to make 870 jets and generate an operating profit of about €7.5 billion ($8.8 billion).  Wall Street was looking for closer to 900 jets and €8.2 billion in operating profit.

headline: NASA Artemis II Mission Is Prepping for Moon Launch. What That Means for SpaceX.
summary: Ahead of a SpaceX IPO, NASA is showing the way things used to be done in space.  It’s a model that won’t likely survive in the suddenly hot commercial space business.  On Thursday, NASA was conducting its “Wet Dress Rehearsal” for the Artemis II mission that will take four astronauts on a 10-day, million-plus-mile journey around the far side of the moon.

headline: Engine Trouble? GE Aerospace Rises While RTX Falls.
